Dow surges nearly 550 points on gains in shares of Pfizer, UnitedHealth

Powered by positive momentum for shares of Pfizer and UnitedHealth, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is soaring Monday afternoon. The Dow DJIA, -1.17% was most recently trading 541 points, or 2.1%, higher, as shares of Pfizer PFE, -0.31% and UnitedHealth UNH, 0.49% have contributed around one third of the index's intraday rally. Pfizer's shares are up $1.75 (5.2%) while those of UnitedHealth have risen $12.01 (4.1%), combining for an approximately 94-point bump for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are Goldman Sachs GS, -1.58%, Caterpillar CAT, -0.26%, and Home Depot HD, -1.54%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the index equates to a 6.86-point swing.

